by deleting SECTION 7 and substituting instead:
SECTION 7. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 2-10-114(b), is amended by adding
the following as a new subdivision (3) and redesignating the existing subdivision (3) accordingly:
(3) Expenditures of campaign funds to defend civil litigation involving the
candidate's nomination for election or election to office is deemed not for personal use.
AND FURTHER AMEND by deleting SECTION 14 and SECTION 15 and substituting instead:
SECTION 14. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 2-10-114(b)(2), is amended by
adding the following new subdivision:
( ) Public relations, consulting, and legal expenses of a candidate or officeholder
concerning a criminal matter involving the candidate or officeholder.
SECTION 15. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 2-10-105(e)(2), is amended by
deleting the language "of all officers" and substituting "at least one (1) officer".
SECTION 16. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 2-10-105(h)(1)(A), is amended by
deleting subdivisions (i)-(iii) and substituting instead:
(i) For a committee participating in the election of a candidate for any statewide
office, five thousand dollars ($5,000); and
(ii) For a committee participating in the election of any other state or local public
office, three thousand dollars ($3,000); and
